FT  07 NOV 94 / Arts (Openings): London
In a hectic week of London theatrical openings, Stephanie Cole comes to the
Comedy Theatre tonight in 'A Passionate Woman'; Brian Cox comes to Riverside
Studios on Thursday in his own production of Ibsen's 'The Master Builder';
and on the same night Mark Rylance and Michael Rudko (swapping the roles of
brothers at alternate performances) come to the Donmar Warehouse in Sam
Shephard's 'True West'.
